16 revising Code Section 20-2-156, relating to program for limited-English-proficient students,
17 as follows:
18 "20-2-156.
19 (a) The State Board of Education shall create a program for limited-English-proficient
20 students whose native language is not English, subject to appropriation by the General
21 Assembly. The purpose of this program is to assist such students to develop proficiency
22 in the English language, including listening, speaking, reading, and writing, sufficient to
23 perform effectively at the currently assigned grade level. The state board shall prescribe
24 such rules and regulations regarding eligibility criteria and standards as may be needed to
25 carry out the provisions of this Code section. The state board shall also prescribe rules and
26 regulations regarding community outreach efforts by local school systems to ensure that
27 limited-English-proficient students and their parents and guardians are provided
28 information regarding the program. This program may also be referred to as the English
29 for speakers of other languages (ESOL) program.
30 (b) The State Board of Education shall establish standards for foreign language interpreters
31 working with students in educational settings. Such standards shall include, but shall not
32 be limited to:
33 (1) Demonstrated proficiency in English and the target language in listening, speaking,
34 and reading domains; and
35 (2) Familiarity with legal concepts related to and service requirements of Part B of the
36 federal Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA) and Section 504 of the federal
37 Rehabilitation Act of 1973, as well as standards for the use of remote interpreter services,
38 including, but not limited to, the conditions under which remote interpreter services may
39 be used to provide high-quality interpreter services.
40 (c) Each local school system shall provide to limited-English-proficient parents and
41 guardians, in a language easily understood by such parents and guardians, information
42 regarding their children relative to the following:
