54 (d) Each local school system shall provide to limited-English-proficient parents and
55 guardians in a language easily understood by such parents and guardians, regarding their
56 children:
57 (1) Information regarding the availability of interpretation services at any meeting with
58 school representatives;
59 (2) An explanation of how parents or guardians can request an interpreter;
60 (3) Notice that a parent or guardian has the right to request that the interpreter serve no
61 other role in the meeting than as an interpreter, and that the local school system should
62 make reasonable efforts to fulfill this request; and
63 (4) A point of contact to address any questions or complaints about interpretation
64 services.
65 (e) For each meeting a school representative has with limited-English-proficient parents
66 and guardians regarding their children, the recorded minutes of such meeting shall reflect:
67 (1) Whether a parent or guardian requested an interpreter, had previously requested
68 interpretation services, or had otherwise indicated that an interpreter was necessary to
69 ensure meaningful parental or guardian involvement in the meeting;
